title: I'm A Celebrity's Keira Maguire has meltdown on first day | Daily Mail Online
text: Share 50 shares 'This is not okay! This is not okay!' she screamed. 'Is this really what it's going to be like the whole like? Just like, "Let's let her f***ing die!"' As the production crew handed her a glass of water, she said stubbornly: 'You don't know what I'm feeling. I think it's in my eye now.' She continued to weep as fellow contestant Dane Swan went ahead and completed a similar challenge with a tank of scorpions. Tantrum: Keira flipped out from the start, saying she would be 'scarred for life' by the challenge Drama: Fellow camper Dane Swan was almost left speechless as he tried to comfort her Gross! Keira also faced a challenge with snakes and cried, 'I can't believe they did that to me!' She cried: 'I can't believe they did that to me. They don't know how much it's burning!' As a medic attended to her, Keira announced: 'I'm going to be scarred for life. I'm not going to forget about anything'. Once back at the camp, Dane said Keira gone 'berserk at the end' and Tegan Martin questioned if they had a diva on their hands. Help! Keira was seen by medics after her meltdown and told the stinging would pass In pain: The reality TV star said she had a 'high threshold for pain' after her recent cosmetic surgery treatments but the challenge was still too much After she'd calmed down, Keira and Kris Smith revealed they already knew each other and have lived in the same area. Dane teased Kris about it, saying the pair were 'cute' and hinting there could be some flirting between them. But Kris quickly refuted it and said he'd 'ruin his life' if Dane kept teasing him about Keira. Keira also decided her bed was to dirty, so she made the couch her new bed, which irritated the others. She did what? Back at the camp, Dane told the other contestants Keira had gone 'berserk' Really? Model Tegan Martin openly questioned if they had a diva on their hands Washing off the day! The Bachelor star finally manged to settle down after a shower Chill out! After she calmed down, Keira revealed she already knows contestant Kris Smith because they have lived in the same area 'I can see what's going to happen here sweetie, it's not going to be good, alright,' Ash Pollard said. 'Too bad, my bed,' Keira snapped as she made herself comfortable on the couch. Ash and Keira clashed again over dinner when Keira asked the My Kitchen Rules star to make potato salad and she replied: 'Babe, there's no mayonnaise or anything, or egg, or onion.' What's going on there? Dane teased Kris about knowing Keira before the jungle, suggesting the pair were 'cute' and hinting there could be some flirting between them No romance here! But Kris quickly refuted the suggestion and said he'd 'ruin his life' if Dane kept teasing him about Keira Amused! Keira clearly enjoyed the camp gossip about her and Kris a lot more than he did Keira later confessed: 'Ash is an alpha female like I am, so I feel like it's a natural thing we may clash'. But she did bond with T'ziporah Malkah, the '90s glamour model formerly known as Kate Fischer. T'ziporah said:, 'I was probably a lot more like her when I was her age. You know, very energetic, very outgoing. I didn't really care what I said.' Drama! Ash and Keira clashed again over dinner when Keira asked Ash to make potato salad Um, what? Ash replied, 'Babe, there's no mayonnaise or anything, or egg, or onion' Camp rivals? Keira later confessed, 'Ash is an alpha female like I am, so I feel like it's a natural thing we may clash' Keira also said of T'ziporah: 'I adore her... I feel like I'm protective over her, because I feel like I understand, you know, why she is the way she is.' Another Tucker Trial was announced for the next episode, and Keira was voted to take part - but she was certainly not happy about it. It remains to be seen how the former real estate professional will cope with the next jungle challenge after her dramatic debut. 'I adore her...
